JUPEB Registration Page

NOTE This registration process is strictly online & ONLY on this website. Also note that; A non-refundable application fee of Ten Thousand naira (₦10,000) will be charge for the registration!
Documents & details that would be required during the registration process includes:
  • Applicant Biodata
  • Parent/Guardian Personal & Contact details
  • O'level Subjects and Grades (Awaiting result is allowed)
  • Passport-Size Photograph (197x257pixels)
  • A Functioning E-mail Address & Phone Number(s).

Applicants Are Expected To Follow This Three(3) Simple Registration Instructions To Complete The Registration Process:

Step

1

Using their full name as REFERENCE; Prospective applicants are to pay a non-refundable application fee of Ten thousand naira (₦10,000) at any nationwide branch of Guranty Trust Bank(GTB) and only to the account with details below:
Account Name: A CLEAR DISTINCTION EDUCATIONAL SERVICES
Account No: 0168351670
Bank: Guaranty Trust Bank (GTB)
Payment May Be Made Through Any Of This Channels: Bank Deposit(Teller), ATM, Mobile & Internet Banking Transfers.

Step

2

After making payment;..Applicants are to CLICK HERE FOR JUPEB FORM and fill in every requested details correctly and with CAPITAL/BLOCK LETTERS, Then Upload a passport size photograph into the designated area of the form.
To validate the payment made in STEP 1 above, also upload your proof of payment(P.O.P) into the form before clicking the submit button. Once the payment has been validated along with your registration, applicants will receive a confirmation email with thier Center Name & Address to the e-mail address used for the registration process.
Proof Of Payment(P.O.P) May Be: Bank Teller, Transfer Slip, Screenshot From Mobile & Internet Banking.

Step

3

Upon completion of candidate's online registration, candidates are expected to PRINT out the Hard-Copy of application slip for attestation by Parent, Sponsor or Guardian! After that applicant may proceed to their respective chosen study centre for clearance and resumption on /or before the date stated on their application printout.

PLEASE NOTE On resumption; students are to come with the Hard-Copy of their registration form, 12 passport-size photographs, 3 copies of their O'level result WAEC/NECO/GCE/NABTEB. If you want to use awaiting result, it is allow too. Also those who made cash deposit through bank tellers are to come along with the teller of the ₦10,000 & the teller of their school fees paid to our account.
To clear any doubt or ambiguity, read our JUPEB Success Stories from our previous candidates at the next section of this page!
